  "response_text": "The formula to calculate the area of a circle is:\n\nArea = \u03c0r\u00b2\n\nWhere r is the radius of the circle.\n\nGiven the radius is 7, we can plug this value into the formula:\n\nArea = \u03c0(7)\u00b2\nArea = \u03c0(49)\nArea \u2248 3.14159 * 49\nArea \u2248 153.93804\n\nSo, the area of the circle with a radius of 7 is approximately 153.94 square units.",
